einer and Ennio Valentinelli greatly extends our knowledge of the movement. Daly’s timely and detailed analysis challenges long-held assumptions about Futurist activity during the war and offers new insights for both the non-specialist and specialist alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aAuthors, ItalianxBiographyx20th centuryxItaly. 0aAuthors, Italiany20th centuryvBiography. 0aFuturism (Literary movement)xItaly. 0aFuturism (Literary movement)zItaly. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xItaly. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xLiterature and the war. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918zItaly. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Italian.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066595640uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144261934040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442619340423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442619340.jpg  a978-3-11-066595-6  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles